**Bandwidth Performance Report**

**Location**: Cyberhub - Gurugram, Gurgaon | **Vendor**: TATA ILL | **Link Type**: ILL | **Business Hours**: 11:00–22:00 | **Provisioned Speed**: 500.0 Mbps

**1. Usage Pattern Analysis**
The WAN link exhibits extremely low average usage at 1.45 Mbps (0.3% utilization) compared to its 500 Mbps provisioned speed. While a peak of 378.92 Mbps (75.8% utilization) was recorded, this is an infrequent burst, as sustained daily peaks average only 7.18 Mbps. The link is consistently under-utilized, operating well below capacity for the vast majority of the time.

**2. Capacity Planning Recommendations**
This link is significantly over-provisioned. Current usage patterns, even at the 99th percentile (17.68 Mbps), are a small fraction of the 500 Mbps capacity. Although usage is increasing at 11.75% monthly, it would take an exceptionally long time to approach 80% capacity. Rightsizing the link should be considered for cost efficiency.

**3. Performance Risks & Bottlenecks**
There are no current performance risks or congestion bottlenecks. The link maintains 100% excellent SLA compliance, with no minutes exceeding 90% capacity. Even the infrequent high bursts do not exceed the provisioned limit or cause service degradation.

**Conclusion**
The current WAN link is substantially over-provisioned and presents a clear opportunity for cost optimization.
